WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:01.479 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:00:01.479 --> 00:00:19.627 align:middle line:90%


00:00:19.627 --> 00:00:21.460 align:middle line:10%
>>REGINA MEREDITH: Many
of you have probably

00:00:21.460 --> 00:00:23.530 align:middle line:10%
heard the term
"sheeple," which simply

00:00:23.530 --> 00:00:26.100 align:middle line:10%
means people who are
led around like sheep.

00:00:26.100 --> 00:00:29.100 align:middle line:10%
The surprising part is that
this term applies to most of us,

00:00:29.100 --> 00:00:30.339 align:middle line:10%
but we don't know it.

00:00:30.339 --> 00:00:31.880 align:middle line:10%
How often have you
wondered why there

00:00:31.880 --> 00:00:33.980 align:middle line:10%
seem to be too few
valid choices when

00:00:33.980 --> 00:00:35.690 align:middle line:10%
it comes to the
things that matter,

00:00:35.690 --> 00:00:38.415 align:middle line:10%
or have had that deflated
feeling of is that all there

00:00:38.415 --> 00:00:39.310 align:middle line:10%
is?

00:00:39.310 --> 00:00:41.300 align:middle line:84%
Investigative
reporter Jon Rappoport

00:00:41.300 --> 00:00:42.860 align:middle line:84%
would tell you
this is by design,

00:00:42.860 --> 00:00:45.700 align:middle line:90%
and it began long, long ago.

00:00:45.700 --> 00:00:46.670 align:middle line:90%
Welcome, Jon.

00:00:46.670 --> 00:00:48.500 align:middle line:84%
>>JON RAPPOPORT:
Nice to be here.

00:00:48.500 --> 00:00:50.250 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Great work.

00:00:50.250 --> 00:00:53.160 align:middle line:84%
This last weekend I
read the earliest one,

00:00:53.160 --> 00:00:56.250 align:middle line:84%
which was The Secret Behind
Secret Societies, which is now

00:00:56.250 --> 00:00:58.530 align:middle line:84%
leading into The
Matrix Revealed, which

00:00:58.530 --> 00:01:03.290 align:middle line:84%
is a CD set, which I haven't had
the opportunity to pick up yet.

00:01:03.290 --> 00:01:05.480 align:middle line:84%
But there's a reason
you're doing this,

00:01:05.480 --> 00:01:08.120 align:middle line:84%
and it really goes back
long ago to some experiences

00:01:08.120 --> 00:01:11.250 align:middle line:84%
you had when you
were a young man who

00:01:11.250 --> 00:01:13.740 align:middle line:84%
came into the acquaintance
of an extraordinary healer.

00:01:13.740 --> 00:01:16.240 align:middle line:84%
And I would like you to just
begin setting yourself up

00:01:16.240 --> 00:01:19.521 align:middle line:84%
so we understand where
you were coming from.

00:01:19.521 --> 00:01:21.270 align:middle line:10%
>>RAPPOPORT: I was 22,
working in New York

00:01:21.270 --> 00:01:23.500 align:middle line:10%
City in a bookstore.

00:01:23.500 --> 00:01:27.460 align:middle line:10%
I was beginning to write
when I wasn't working.

00:01:27.460 --> 00:01:29.950 align:middle line:10%
A guy came into the store
and asked for a book.

00:01:29.950 --> 00:01:31.180 align:middle line:10%
We had a conversation.

00:01:31.180 --> 00:01:36.780 align:middle line:10%
The next thing I knew, we sat
down, we had lunch together.

00:01:36.780 --> 00:01:41.930 align:middle line:10%
This was 1960, '61
in New York City.

00:01:41.930 --> 00:01:45.500 align:middle line:84%
And he tells me
that he's a healer.

00:01:45.500 --> 00:01:49.679 align:middle line:84%
Well, if you lived in
1961, nobody said that.

00:01:49.679 --> 00:01:50.970 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: No, nobody said that.

00:01:50.970 --> 00:01:51.700 align:middle line:84%
>>RAPPOPORT: And
even if they did,

00:01:51.700 --> 00:01:53.730 align:middle line:84%
you would say, well, I
don't know what you mean,

00:01:53.730 --> 00:01:56.572 align:middle line:90%
or you're crazy, or both.

00:01:56.572 --> 00:01:58.280 align:middle line:84%
I said, well, what
are you talking about?

00:01:58.280 --> 00:01:59.850 align:middle line:84%
So he started talking
to me about all

00:01:59.850 --> 00:02:01.980 align:middle line:84%
sorts of things--
Freud, Wilhelm Reich,

00:02:01.980 --> 00:02:07.910 align:middle line:84%
all kinds of what he
would call healers.

00:02:07.910 --> 00:02:10.669 align:middle line:84%
But the gist of it was that
in his apartment in Manhattan,

00:02:10.669 --> 00:02:13.864 align:middle line:84%
he was working on
diplomats at the UN.

00:02:13.864 --> 00:02:15.530 align:middle line:84%
They were coming to
see him because they

00:02:15.530 --> 00:02:17.630 align:middle line:90%
had physical problems.

00:02:17.630 --> 00:02:20.530 align:middle line:84%
And he was curing them
of those problems.

00:02:20.530 --> 00:02:21.860 align:middle line:90%
That was what I observed.

00:02:21.860 --> 00:02:24.620 align:middle line:84%
That's what eventually, through
our friendship, Richard Jenkins

00:02:24.620 --> 00:02:27.680 align:middle line:90%
and I became friends.

00:02:27.680 --> 00:02:28.890 align:middle line:90%
We talked a great deal.

00:02:28.890 --> 00:02:32.530 align:middle line:84%
He said, come in,
watch what I do.

00:02:32.530 --> 00:02:33.720 align:middle line:90%
I said, OK.

00:02:33.720 --> 00:02:36.030 align:middle line:84%
So I would sit
there, and I would

00:02:36.030 --> 00:02:38.370 align:middle line:90%
watch him work on these people.

00:02:38.370 --> 00:02:41.750 align:middle line:90%


00:02:41.750 --> 00:02:45.360 align:middle line:84%
There was nothing to
recognize about it.

00:02:45.360 --> 00:02:49.590 align:middle line:84%
There was no style where you
would say, ah, yes, well, you

00:02:49.590 --> 00:02:53.120 align:middle line:90%
are of the school of so-and-so.

00:02:53.120 --> 00:02:55.100 align:middle line:90%
There was none of that.

00:02:55.100 --> 00:02:57.135 align:middle line:84%
And this is part
of the point why

00:02:57.135 --> 00:03:01.800 align:middle line:84%
I started Secret Behind Secret
Societies with this story--

00:03:01.800 --> 00:03:07.420 align:middle line:84%
because people are
bulldozed and fooled

00:03:07.420 --> 00:03:12.520 align:middle line:84%
into accepting
spiritual formula.

00:03:12.520 --> 00:03:14.240 align:middle line:90%
This is the world of the spirit.

00:03:14.240 --> 00:03:15.680 align:middle line:90%
This is the world of the spirit.

00:03:15.680 --> 00:03:18.635 align:middle line:84%
Well, the pedigree of
this author is so-and-so,

00:03:18.635 --> 00:03:20.510 align:middle line:84%
and it comes from a
tradition that goes back,

00:03:20.510 --> 00:03:22.400 align:middle line:84%
and therefore it
must be fantastic.

00:03:22.400 --> 00:03:24.520 align:middle line:84%
Or this comes from
this country, which

00:03:24.520 --> 00:03:28.210 align:middle line:90%
we know has had magnificent--

00:03:28.210 --> 00:03:30.730 align:middle line:84%
What's going on
here is that people

00:03:30.730 --> 00:03:34.884 align:middle line:84%
have lost totally
the individual sense

00:03:34.884 --> 00:03:41.900 align:middle line:90%
of what would make me unique.

00:03:41.900 --> 00:03:44.920 align:middle line:84%
What would make my
contribution unique?

00:03:44.920 --> 00:03:47.330 align:middle line:84%
What Richard Jenkins was
telling me and showing me

00:03:47.330 --> 00:03:50.820 align:middle line:84%
by his actions
with these people--

00:03:50.820 --> 00:03:52.210 align:middle line:90%
he would move around the table.

00:03:52.210 --> 00:03:56.780 align:middle line:84%
He'd have a guy laying out on
a table-- diplomat at the UN.

00:03:56.780 --> 00:03:58.480 align:middle line:84%
Maybe he spoke English,
maybe he didn't.

00:03:58.480 --> 00:03:59.280 align:middle line:90%
It didn't matter.

00:03:59.280 --> 00:04:04.500 align:middle line:84%
Richard would move around the
table, kind of like a dancer,

00:04:04.500 --> 00:04:06.970 align:middle line:84%
but he wasn't
following a pattern.

00:04:06.970 --> 00:04:08.110 align:middle line:90%
He was improvising.

00:04:08.110 --> 00:04:11.410 align:middle line:84%
This became clear to me in
about the second session.

00:04:11.410 --> 00:04:17.299 align:middle line:84%
This guy's improvising,
which on first blush

00:04:17.299 --> 00:04:20.269 align:middle line:84%
seems to be therefore,
he has absolutely no idea

00:04:20.269 --> 00:04:21.500 align:middle line:90%
what he's doing.

00:04:21.500 --> 00:04:23.200 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And that was your
first thought, I would imagine.

00:04:23.200 --> 00:04:25.033 align:middle line:84%
>>RAPPOPORT: Yeah, he
has absolutely no idea

00:04:25.033 --> 00:04:26.170 align:middle line:90%
what he's doing.

00:04:26.170 --> 00:04:27.770 align:middle line:84%
So why, at the end
of the session,

00:04:27.770 --> 00:04:29.340 align:middle line:90%
does the guy feel better?

00:04:29.340 --> 00:04:30.390 align:middle line:90%
They're not talking.

00:04:30.390 --> 00:04:32.100 align:middle line:84%
Richard is not making
any suggestions.

00:04:32.100 --> 00:04:33.439 align:middle line:90%
There's no influence here.

00:04:33.439 --> 00:04:35.480 align:middle line:84%
The guy's lying on his
back with his eyes closed,

00:04:35.480 --> 00:04:38.050 align:middle line:84%
and Richard is moving
around the table--

00:04:38.050 --> 00:04:40.790 align:middle line:84%
movements of different
kinds-- seems

00:04:40.790 --> 00:04:43.090 align:middle line:84%
to be part of the
time in his own world.

00:04:43.090 --> 00:04:44.880 align:middle line:84%
Occasionally he puts
his hand somewhere

00:04:44.880 --> 00:04:47.700 align:middle line:90%
on the body of this guy.

00:04:47.700 --> 00:04:50.420 align:middle line:90%


00:04:50.420 --> 00:04:55.110 align:middle line:84%
I watched sessions
progress on the same person

00:04:55.110 --> 00:04:57.680 align:middle line:90%
week after week after week.

00:04:57.680 --> 00:05:00.860 align:middle line:90%
Arthritis begins to dissolve.

00:05:00.860 --> 00:05:03.280 align:middle line:84%
Serious organ problems
begin to go away.

00:05:03.280 --> 00:05:06.630 align:middle line:84%
All sorts of physical
manifestations

00:05:06.630 --> 00:05:12.110 align:middle line:84%
change, and all I can see is
that this guy's improvising.

00:05:12.110 --> 00:05:17.020 align:middle line:84%
Well, this not only I found
curious but fantastically

00:05:17.020 --> 00:05:21.660 align:middle line:84%
interesting because that's what
I was trying to do as a writer.

00:05:21.660 --> 00:05:23.750 align:middle line:90%
I started to paint then.

00:05:23.750 --> 00:05:26.650 align:middle line:84%
That's what I was trying
to do as a painter.

00:05:26.650 --> 00:05:27.840 align:middle line:90%
I loved jazz.

00:05:27.840 --> 00:05:31.580 align:middle line:84%
That's what jazz was all
about-- improvisation,

00:05:31.580 --> 00:05:34.760 align:middle line:84%
spontaneity, what's
happening now in the moment.

00:05:34.760 --> 00:05:36.430 align:middle line:84%
And here, I suddenly
see a guy who

00:05:36.430 --> 00:05:40.810 align:middle line:84%
was a healer-- a category
that I never even imagined

00:05:40.810 --> 00:05:43.240 align:middle line:84%
existed before-- and he
is doing the same thing.

00:05:43.240 --> 00:05:44.170 align:middle line:90%
He's improvising.

00:05:44.170 --> 00:05:46.190 align:middle line:84%
Only now I find
it very difficult

00:05:46.190 --> 00:05:48.900 align:middle line:84%
to believe that there could
be any connection between what

00:05:48.900 --> 00:05:50.630 align:middle line:84%
he's doing and
people being healed.

00:05:50.630 --> 00:05:53.610 align:middle line:84%
And so that became the
basis of the conversations

00:05:53.610 --> 00:05:54.830 align:middle line:90%
that Richard and I had.

00:05:54.830 --> 00:05:58.850 align:middle line:84%
Why do you think what I'm doing,
he would say, has no bearing

00:05:58.850 --> 00:06:01.620 align:middle line:84%
or would have no bearing on
the health of these people?

00:06:01.620 --> 00:06:03.510 align:middle line:84%
I say, you're not
actually doing anything.

00:06:03.510 --> 00:06:04.810 align:middle line:90%
What are you doing?

00:06:04.810 --> 00:06:09.130 align:middle line:84%
You're not twisting, you're not
pressing, you're not inserting.

00:06:09.130 --> 00:06:11.670 align:middle line:90%
You're not doing anything.

00:06:11.670 --> 00:06:14.460 align:middle line:84%
What do you think
anything means?

00:06:14.460 --> 00:06:16.690 align:middle line:84%
Do you think it's
more efficacious

00:06:16.690 --> 00:06:20.660 align:middle line:84%
if I put my hand there on
a person and I concentrate?

00:06:20.660 --> 00:06:22.430 align:middle line:84%
Is that what you're
saying, really?

00:06:22.430 --> 00:06:24.544 align:middle line:84%
And then I'd say, no,
that's not what I'm saying.

00:06:24.544 --> 00:06:25.960 align:middle line:84%
Well, what do you
think I'm doing?

00:06:25.960 --> 00:06:29.620 align:middle line:84%
And this would go on and
on until finally, he said,

00:06:29.620 --> 00:06:32.190 align:middle line:90%
you know what's going on.

00:06:32.190 --> 00:06:34.590 align:middle line:84%
It's why I told you
to come watch this.

00:06:34.590 --> 00:06:38.990 align:middle line:84%
He said, I know where you're
coming from-- improvisation,

00:06:38.990 --> 00:06:42.780 align:middle line:90%
spontaneity, life in the moment.

00:06:42.780 --> 00:06:44.900 align:middle line:84%
This is what you're
aiming for, right?

00:06:44.900 --> 00:06:46.240 align:middle line:90%
This is what you want, isn't it?

00:06:46.240 --> 00:06:46.827 align:middle line:90%
I said, yeah.

00:06:46.827 --> 00:06:48.660 align:middle line:84%
He said, well, this is
what I'm showing you.

00:06:48.660 --> 00:06:49.890 align:middle line:90%
This is what it is.

00:06:49.890 --> 00:06:51.890 align:middle line:84%
He said, you just
don't understand

00:06:51.890 --> 00:06:55.230 align:middle line:84%
the dimensions to
which that can expand

00:06:55.230 --> 00:06:57.960 align:middle line:84%
or the effects that it
can have when you're truly

00:06:57.960 --> 00:07:00.140 align:middle line:90%
acting in the moment right now.

00:07:00.140 --> 00:07:02.840 align:middle line:84%
And this turned around
completely my whole view,

00:07:02.840 --> 00:07:04.500 align:middle line:84%
eventually, of
spirituality, which

00:07:04.500 --> 00:07:07.701 align:middle line:84%
is what I write about in The
Secret Behind Secret Societies.

00:07:07.701 --> 00:07:09.950 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Because spirituality--
even though it sounds

00:07:09.950 --> 00:07:14.180 align:middle line:84%
like it might be a conspiracy
book, the reality is it's not.

00:07:14.180 --> 00:07:16.540 align:middle line:84%
It's a journey of
consciousness and showing how

00:07:16.540 --> 00:07:21.820 align:middle line:84%
our consciousness has been shoe
horned and co-opted to where we

00:07:21.820 --> 00:07:25.410 align:middle line:84%
really do feel as though
we don't have anything

00:07:25.410 --> 00:07:27.030 align:middle line:84%
particularly unique
about ourselves,

00:07:27.030 --> 00:07:30.990 align:middle line:84%
where we can go to a doctor, and
he can do a one-size-fits-all--

00:07:30.990 --> 00:07:34.250 align:middle line:84%
slap some kind of therapy or
slap some kind of drug over

00:07:34.250 --> 00:07:38.270 align:middle line:84%
the top of us and it's going to
work, when in fact we're all--

00:07:38.270 --> 00:07:41.330 align:middle line:84%
I mean, I guess if you
could look at the aura,

00:07:41.330 --> 00:07:44.850 align:middle line:84%
we're all in a state of
constant creation and flux.

00:07:44.850 --> 00:07:47.970 align:middle line:90%
We're all very highly unique.

00:07:47.970 --> 00:07:50.420 align:middle line:84%
And all of that you
were trying to connect

00:07:50.420 --> 00:07:52.527 align:middle line:84%
with through this
healing art of his.

00:07:52.527 --> 00:07:54.360 align:middle line:84%
>>RAPPOPORT: That's
what I was trying to do.

00:07:54.360 --> 00:07:56.068 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And this
whole analogy that you

00:07:56.068 --> 00:07:59.520 align:middle line:84%
used throughout this book of
life being nothing but art,

00:07:59.520 --> 00:08:01.970 align:middle line:90%
I loved.

00:08:01.970 --> 00:08:02.730 align:middle line:90%
I can see that.

00:08:02.730 --> 00:08:03.660 align:middle line:90%
I relate to it.

00:08:03.660 --> 00:08:04.060 align:middle line:90%
>>RAPPOPORT: Me, too.

00:08:04.060 --> 00:08:04.970 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And then
there was one--

00:08:04.970 --> 00:08:06.677 align:middle line:84%
I interviewed Don
Miguel Ruiz, and I'm

00:08:06.677 --> 00:08:08.760 align:middle line:84%
going to say this one
thing, because it's a segue.

00:08:08.760 --> 00:08:11.380 align:middle line:84%
It fits perfectly
into this part of it.

00:08:11.380 --> 00:08:13.890 align:middle line:84%
And he was saying in
his most recent book

00:08:13.890 --> 00:08:17.160 align:middle line:90%
that this is your canvas.

00:08:17.160 --> 00:08:19.630 align:middle line:84%
Don't let anyone else
throw poo or anything else

00:08:19.630 --> 00:08:20.590 align:middle line:90%
on your canvas.

00:08:20.590 --> 00:08:23.430 align:middle line:84%
You should have the
right to wake up each day

00:08:23.430 --> 00:08:26.960 align:middle line:90%
and create anew on your canvas.

00:08:26.960 --> 00:08:31.230 align:middle line:84%
And that's really the whole
point of what you've done here.

00:08:31.230 --> 00:08:35.370 align:middle line:84%
>>RAPPOPORT: Spiritual
life-- people

00:08:35.370 --> 00:08:39.049 align:middle line:84%
have so many ideas
about what it is.

00:08:39.049 --> 00:08:44.100 align:middle line:84%
Most of those ideas inevitably
wind up in something passive

00:08:44.100 --> 00:08:45.920 align:middle line:90%
somehow.

00:08:45.920 --> 00:08:47.880 align:middle line:90%
I'm receiving this.

00:08:47.880 --> 00:08:49.140 align:middle line:90%
This is coming in to me.

00:08:49.140 --> 00:08:52.420 align:middle line:84%
I'm part of a
collective of something.

00:08:52.420 --> 00:08:54.690 align:middle line:90%
It's gooey.

00:08:54.690 --> 00:08:56.550 align:middle line:90%
It's gooey.

00:08:56.550 --> 00:09:01.489 align:middle line:84%
It feels like something's melted
and somebody stuck in there

00:09:01.489 --> 00:09:03.280 align:middle line:84%
and is smiling about
it, saying, well, this

00:09:03.280 --> 00:09:05.029 align:middle line:84%
is exactly where I've
always wanted to be,

00:09:05.029 --> 00:09:06.140 align:middle line:90%
in the collective goo.

00:09:06.140 --> 00:09:07.590 align:middle line:90%
This is where we're going.

00:09:07.590 --> 00:09:09.570 align:middle line:84%
We're going to the
collective goo.

00:09:09.570 --> 00:09:11.080 align:middle line:90%
Hop on board.

00:09:11.080 --> 00:09:12.587 align:middle line:90%
And it's going to be wonderful.

00:09:12.587 --> 00:09:13.670 align:middle line:90%
It's going to be paradise.

00:09:13.670 --> 00:09:16.330 align:middle line:84%
But you won't have to
do anything, really.

00:09:16.330 --> 00:09:18.640 align:middle line:84%
When you finally arrive
there-- yes, there

00:09:18.640 --> 00:09:20.900 align:middle line:84%
may have been strenuous
moments, but you're now there,

00:09:20.900 --> 00:09:22.727 align:middle line:90%
and therefore, you're set.

00:09:22.727 --> 00:09:24.310 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Isn't this
the great promise

00:09:24.310 --> 00:09:26.269 align:middle line:84%
of all of the world's
religions in essence.

00:09:26.269 --> 00:09:27.560 align:middle line:90%
>>RAPPOPORT: Every one of them.

00:09:27.560 --> 00:09:28.480 align:middle line:84%
Every one of them
is based on this.

00:09:28.480 --> 00:09:30.315 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: New Age, Old
Age-- it doesn't matter.

00:09:30.315 --> 00:09:31.280 align:middle line:84%
>>RAPPOPORT: Middle
Age-- it doesn't matter.

00:09:31.280 --> 00:09:32.446 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: It doesn't matter.

00:09:32.446 --> 00:09:36.500 align:middle line:84%
>>RAPPOPORT: Youth-- they're
all based on the same idea.

00:09:36.500 --> 00:09:43.190 align:middle line:84%
It's you're the receiver
getting the transmission.

00:09:43.190 --> 00:09:45.430 align:middle line:84%
If you can't get the
right transmission,

00:09:45.430 --> 00:09:49.940 align:middle line:84%
you have to clear the airwaves,
and then it will come to you.

